    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s03.2.14" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Intake Throttle Valve (ITV)</title>
        <figure id="f3450003017" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM09/M09125.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Intake throttle housing assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>The ITV, a variable position actuator, restricts intake air flow to help heat the exhaust after treatment
            during regeneration. The ITV changes valve position in response to ECM signals. The ITV contains an internal
            position sensor that monitors valve position and transmits a position signal to the ECM. The ITV is mounted
            on the Exhaust Gas Recirculating (EGR) valve elbow housing on the top front of the engine.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
